          <td width="100%"> 
            <h1><a name="gen">Topics in Chronicling America - Labor Day</a></h1>
            <p><font color="#336699"><i>&quot;Labor's Monster Parade! The First Workingmen's Holiday to be Fitly Observed!&quot;.    Read more about it!</i></font></p>
            <p>The information and sample article links below provide access to a sampling of articles from historic newspapers that can be found in the <em>Chronicling America: American Historic Newspapers</em> digital collection (<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/">http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/</a>). Use the Suggested Search Terms and Dates to explore this topic further in Chronicling America.
            </p>
            <hr>
<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85058130/1906-09-03/ed-1/seq-1/"><img src="images/labor.gif" alt="Picture" align="right" border="0" height="189" hspace="10" vspace="10" width="134"></a>
            <p><strong>Jump to:</strong> <a href="#links">Sample Articles</a></p>
            <h3><strong>Important Dates:</strong></h3>
            <ul>
              <LI>September 5, 1882.	The first Labor Day holiday, planned by of the Central Labor Union, is celebrated on a Tuesday in New York City.             
              <LI>June 28, 1894.	Congress enacts a law to make Labor Day a national holiday, to be observed the first Monday in September.
            
            </ul>
            <h3><strong>Suggested Search Strategies:</strong></h3>
            <ul>
              <li><EM>[Try the following terms in combination, proximity, or as 
                phrases using <A 
              href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/">Search 
                  Pages</A> in Chronicling America.] </EM>labor holiday, labor day, parade, union.</li>
              <li>	It is important to use a specific date range if looking for articles for a particular event in order to narrow your results. </li>
            </ul>
            <hr>
            <h2><a name="links"></a>Sample Articles  from Chronicling America: </h2>
			
        <ul>

<li>"<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030214/1882-09-07/ed-1/seq-4/;words=parade+IABOB+DE+labor+3+IOXSTRATIOX?date1=1882&date2=1882&searchType=advanced&lccn=&proxdistance=50&state=New+York&rows=20&ortext=&proxtext=labor+parade&phrasetext=IABOB&andtext=DE3IOXSTRATIOX&dateFilterType=yearRange&index=0">A Labor Demonstration</a>,"
<em>New-York Tribune</em> (New York, NY),
September 7, 1882, Page 4, Image 4, col. 4.</li>

<li>"<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030272/1884-09-01/ed-1/seq-1/;words=Labor+laborers+LABORS+PARADE+labor?date1=08%2F31%2F1884&date2=09%2F14%2F1884&searchType=advanced&lccn=&proxdistance=5&state=&rows=20&ortext=&proxtext=labor+parade&phrasetext=&andtext=labor&dateFilterType=range&index=8">Labor's Monster Parade</a>,"
<em>The Sun</em> (New York, NY),
September 1, 1884, Page 1, Image 1, col. 3.</li>

<li>"<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn90059522/1885-09-08/ed-1/seq-2/;words=Holiday+Union+labor+unions+Labor+holiday?date1=08%2F30%2F1885&date2=09%2F13%2F1885&searchType=advanced&lccn=&proxdistance=5&state=&rows=20&ortext=&proxtext=union+labor&phrasetext=&andtext=holiday&dateFilterType=range&index=1">The Workingmen's Picnic</a>,"
<em>St. Paul Daily Globe</em> (Saint Paul, MN),
September 8, 1885, Page 2, Image 2, col. 2-3.</li>

<li>"<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83040340/1894-08-31/ed-1/seq-8/;words=congress+Congress+NATIONAL+Labors+Laboring+labor+laboring+Labor+LABOR+DAY?date1=07%2F01%2F1894&rows=20&searchType=advanced&proxdistance=5&date2=08%2F31%2F1894&ortext=&proxtext=&phrasetext=national+labor+day&andtext=congress+labor&dateFilterType=range&index=0">Nation's Labor Day</a>,"
<em>The Iola Register</em> (Iola, KS),
August 31, 1894, Page 8, Image 8, col. 1-2.</li>

<li>"<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn94052989/1894-09-03/ed-1/seq-4/;words=national+laboring+labor+labored+Labor+LABOR+day?date1=07%2F01%2F1894&rows=20&searchType=advanced&proxdistance=5&date2=09%2F16%2F1894&ortext=&proxtext=&phrasetext=national+labor+day&andtext=labor&dateFilterType=range&index=4">Labor Will Rest</a>,"
<em>The Morning Call</em> (San Francisco, CA),
September 3, 1894, Page 3, Image 4, col. 5.</li>

<li>"<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn87060190/1900-09-04/ed-1/seq-1/;words=celebrated+parade+Celebrated+Labor+celebrating+Day+celebration?date1=1900&date2=1922&searchType=advanced&lccn=&proxdistance=5&state=&rows=20&ortext=&proxtext=&phrasetext=labor+day&andtext=parade+celebration&dateFilterType=yearRange&index=18">Rest and Recreation</a>,"
<em>The Evening Bulletin</em> (Maysville, KY),
September 4, 1900, Page 1, Image 1, col. 1-2.</li>

<li>"<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83025121/1901-09-03/ed-1/seq-1/;words=celebrated+PARADE+paraders+CELEBRATED+Day+LABOR+parade+celebrating+parades+labor+Labor+DAY+day+celebration?date1=1900&sort=relevance&date2=1922&searchType=advanced&lccn=&proxdistance=5&state=&rows=20&ortext=&proxtext=&phrasetext=labor+day&andtext=parade+celebration&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=2&index=3">Parade of the Union Workmen</a>,"
<em>The Hawaiian Gazette</em> (Honolululu, HI),
September 3, 1901, Page 1, Image 1, col. 1-5.</li>

<li>"<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83045555/1901-09-02/ed-1/seq-1/;words=celebrations+laborer+workingman+DAY+celebrated+laboring+LABOR+laborers+labor+Labor+Day+day+celebration?date1=1900&sort=relevance&date2=1922&searchType=advanced&lccn=&proxdistance=5&state=&rows=20&ortext=&proxtext=&phrasetext=labor+day&andtext=workingman+labor+celebrate&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=2&index=17">Finest Labor Demonstration in the City's History</a>,"
<em>Deseret Evening News</em> (Great Salt City, UT),
September 2, 1901, Page 1, Image 1, col. 3-6.</li>

<li>"<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn84020274/1902-09-02/ed-1/seq-5/;words=PARADE+CELEBRATION+paraded+celebrated+PARADES+celebration+DAY+parade+Celebration+parades+paraders+LABOR+Labor+CELEBRATES+Day+Parade?date1=1900&sort=relevance&date2=1922&searchType=advanced&lccn=&proxdistance=5&state=&rows=20&ortext=&proxtext=&phrasetext=labor+day&andtext=parade+celebration&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=2&index=1">Big Parade Characterized This Holiday Celebration</a>,"
<em>The St. Louis Republic</em> (St. Louis, MO),
September 2, 1902, Page 5, Image 5, col. 1-2.</li>

<li>"<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85058130/1906-09-03/ed-1/seq-1/;words=Day+workingmans+LABOR+labor+Labor+day+celebrate+celebration?date1=1900&sort=relevance&sort=relevance&date2=1922&searchType=advanced&lccn=&proxdistance=5&state=&rows=20&ortext=&proxtext=&phrasetext=labor+day&andtext=workingman+labor+celebrate&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=2&page=3&index=0">Union Labor Will Celebrate</a>,"
<em>The Salt Lake Herald</em> (Salt Lake City, UT),
September 3, 1906, Page 1, Image 1, col. 7.</li>

</ul>
			
